description:
GOAL:
Create a data transformation layer that converts BeadIssue objects into SocialCard objects for the Social view.

PROBLEM:
The Social view needs cards that show:
- Task ID and title
- Blocked-by (UNLOCKS) with status
- Blocking (BLOCKS) with status
- Assigned agents with liveness
- Last activity message
- Epic context

We need to transform raw BeadIssue data into this format efficiently.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
1. buildSocialCards function created in src/lib/social-cards.ts
2. Returns array of SocialCard objects
3. Correctly computes blocked-by and blocking relationships
4. Includes agent liveness from registry
5. Includes last activity from activity feed
6. Unit tests for transformation logic
7. npm run typecheck passes
8. npm run lint passes
9. npm run test passes

IMPLEMENTATION STEPS:
1. Create src/lib/social-cards.ts
2. Define SocialCard interface
3. Implement buildSocialCards function
4. Integrate with agent-registry for liveness
5. Integrate with activity for last message
6. Write unit tests

FILES TO CREATE:
- src/lib/social-cards.ts
- tests/lib/social-cards.test.ts

INTERFACE:

```typescript
interface SocialCard {
  id: string;                    // Task ID
  title: string;
  status: 'ready' | 'in_progress' | 'blocked' | 'closed';
  priority: number;

  // Blocks/Unlocks
  blockedBy: {
    id: string;
    title: string;
    status: string;
  }[];
  blocking: {
    id: string;
    title: string;
    status: string;
  }[];

  // Agents
  assignee: string | null;
  agents: {
    id: string;
    liveness: AgentLiveness;
  }[];

  // Activity
  lastActivity: {
    message: string;
    author: string;
    timestamp: string;
  } | null;

  // Metadata
  epicId: string | null;
  updatedAt: string;
}

function buildSocialCards(
  issues: BeadIssue[],
  options?: {
    agentLiveness?: Record<string, AgentLiveness>;
    recentActivity?: Map<string, ActivityEvent>;
  }
): SocialCard[];
```

REUSE:
- src/lib/agent-sessions.ts (patterns for aggregation)
- src/lib/activity.ts (for last activity)

SKILLS TO USE:
- verification-before-completion
- test-driven-development
- linus-beads-discipline

DEPENDENCIES:
- Uses existing: agent-registry, activity

VERIFICATION:
```bash
npm run typecheck
npm run lint
npm run test
```

EVIDENCE TO CAPTURE:
- Test output showing transformation works
- npm run typecheck output

GOAL:
Create the main unified shell component that replaces the current page.tsx with a 3-panel CSS grid layout.

PROBLEM:
Current page.tsx renders a single view. We need a shell that:
- Renders 3 panels (left nav, middle content, right detail)
- Switches between views (Social, Graph, Swarm) via tabs
- Uses URL state for view selection
- Provides responsive behavior

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
1. UnifiedShell component created in src/app/page.tsx (rename existing to page-old.tsx first)
2. CSS Grid layout with 3 columns (13rem, 1fr, 17rem on desktop)
3. View tabs switch middle content
4. URL state hook integrated for view selection
5. Works with existing data fetching
6. npm run typecheck passes
7. npm run lint passes

IMPLEMENTATION STEPS:
1. Copy src/app/page.tsx to src/app/page-old.tsx
2. Create new src/app/page.tsx with UnifiedShell
3. Import useUrlState hook
4. Set up CSS Grid layout
5. Add view tab navigation
6. Create placeholder content for each view
7. Test responsive behavior

FILES TO MODIFY/CREATE:
- src/app/page.tsx (NEW - UnifiedShell)
- src/app/page-old.tsx (COPY - reference)

COMPONENT STRUCTURE:

```typescript
// src/app/page.tsx
export default async function Page(props: PageProps) {
  // Server-side data fetching (same as current)
  const issues = await readIssuesForScope(...);

  return (
    <UnifiedShell
      issues={issues}
      projectRoot={...}
      projectScopeKey={...}
      projectScopeOptions={...}
      projectScopeMode={...}
    />
  );
}

// Client component
'use client';
function UnifiedShell(props: UnifiedShellProps) {
  const { view, setView } = useUrlState();

  return (
    <div className="grid h-screen grid-cols-[13rem_1fr_17rem]">\n      <LeftPanel />
      <main className="flex flex-col">
        <TopBar view={view} setView={setView} />\n        <ViewContent view={view} {...props} />\n      </main>
      <RightPanel />
    </div>
  );
}
```

LAYOUT CSS:
```css
/* Desktop */
grid-template-columns: 13rem 1fr 17rem;

/* Tablet (< 1024px) */
grid-template-columns: 10rem 1fr;

/* Mobile (< 768px) */
grid-template-columns: 1fr;
```

SKILLS TO USE:
- verification-before-completion: Run verification commands
- test-driven-development: Not required for layout setup
- linus-beads-discipline: Keep changes minimal

DEPENDENCIES:
- Requires: 0.1 (tokens), 0.2 (shadcn), 0.3 (primitives), 1.1 (URL state)

VERIFICATION:
```bash
npm run typecheck
npm run lint
# Visual check: shell renders with 3 panels
```

EVIDENCE TO CAPTURE:
- Screenshot of shell layout
- npm run typecheck output

GOAL:
Integrate responsive behavior across all shell components and verify correct display at all breakpoints.

PROBLEM:
We have individual components with responsive behavior, but need to ensure they work together correctly at:
- Mobile (< 768px)
- Tablet (768px - 1024px)
- Desktop (≥ 1024px)
- Ultrawide (≥ 1536px)

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
1. All breakpoints render correctly
2. Left panel collapses on tablet, hidden on mobile
3. Right panel is sidebar on desktop, slide-over on tablet, drawer on mobile
4. Top bar remains visible at all sizes
5. Card grid adjusts columns appropriately
6. Screenshots captured at 390px, 768px, 1440px
7. npm run typecheck passes
8. npm run lint passes

IMPLEMENTATION STEPS:
1. Create src/hooks/use-responsive.ts for breakpoint detection
2. Integrate responsive hook into UnifiedShell
3. Add conditional rendering for panels
4. Test all breakpoints manually
5. Capture screenshots

FILES TO CREATE/MODIFY:
- src/hooks/use-responsive.ts (NEW)
- src/app/page.tsx (modify UnifiedShell)

HOOK INTERFACE:

```typescript
interface ResponsiveState {
  breakpoint: 'mobile' | 'tablet' | 'desktop' | 'ultrawide';
  isMobile: boolean;
  isTablet: boolean;
  isDesktop: boolean;
  isUltrawide: boolean;
  leftPanelCollapsed: boolean;
  rightPanelAsDrawer: boolean;
}

function useResponsive(): ResponsiveState;
```

BREAKPOINT LOGIC:

```typescript
const BREAKPOINTS = {
  mobile: 768,
  tablet: 1024,
  ultrawide: 1536,
};

// Mobile: < 768px
// - Left panel: hidden
// - Right panel: full-screen drawer
// - Card grid: 1 column

// Tablet: 768px - 1024px
// - Left panel: collapsed (icon only)
// - Right panel: slide-over from right
// - Card grid: 2 columns

// Desktop: 1024px - 1536px
// - Left panel: visible (13rem)
// - Right panel: sidebar (17rem)
// - Card grid: 3 columns

// Ultrawide: >= 1536px
// - Left panel: visible (13rem)
// - Right panel: sidebar (17rem)
// - Card grid: 4+ columns
```

SKILLS TO USE:
- verification-before-completion
- linus-beads-discipline

DEPENDENCIES:
- Requires: 1.3, 1.4, 1.5 (all shell components)

VERIFICATION:
```bash
npm run typecheck
npm run lint
# Visual check at all breakpoints
# Screenshots: artifacts/shell-390.png, shell-768.png, shell-1440.png
```

EVIDENCE TO CAPTURE:
- Screenshots at 390px, 768px, 1440px
- npm run typecheck output
- npm run lint output

GOAL:
Create the base reusable primitive components that will be used across all views (Social, Graph, Swarm).

PROBLEM:
We need shared components for the unified shell: card base, agent avatar with status, progress bar, view-jump icons, and last activity display. These should use shadcn/ui primitives and the new earthy-dark tokens.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
1. BaseCard component created with consistent styling
2. AgentAvatar component with liveness status glow
3. ProgressBar component for swarm progress visualization
4. ViewJumpIcons component ([≡] [◊] [≋] buttons)
5. LastActivity component for activity preview
6. All components have TypeScript types
7. Unit tests for each component
8. npm run typecheck passes
9. npm run lint passes
10. npm run test passes

IMPLEMENTATION STEPS:
1. Create src/components/shared/ directory
2. Implement BaseCard using shadcn Card
3. Implement AgentAvatar with status glow CSS
4. Implement ProgressBar with Tailwind
5. Implement ViewJumpIcons with icons
6. Implement LastActivity with timestamp formatting
7. Write unit tests for each

FILES TO CREATE:
- src/components/shared/base-card.tsx
- src/components/shared/agent-avatar.tsx
- src/components/shared/progress-bar.tsx
- src/components/shared/view-jump-icons.tsx
- src/components/shared/last-activity.tsx
- src/components/shared/index.ts (exports)
- tests/components/shared/base-card.test.tsx
- tests/components/shared/agent-avatar.test.tsx
- tests/components/shared/progress-bar.test.tsx

COMPONENT INTERFACES:

```typescript
